{
  "texts": [
    "We use the Mars_Lunar crater dataset, which contains 143 images and corresponding labels in YOLO v5 PyTorch format, exported from Roboflow 33.",
    "In the proposed model custom implementation of the semantic segmentation U-Net architecture is performed.",
    "Using a symmetric expanding path to permit exact localization and a contracting path to collect context, U-Net is a popular deep-learning architecture for image segmentation problems.",
    "ResNet18, a well-liked deep convolutional neural network design with better accuracy while training on huge datasets than earlier models, serves as the foundation for this application.",
    "The model is optimized for the particular purpose of semantic segmentation using a cross-entropy loss function, having been pre-trained on ImageNet."
  ]
}